This paper deals with the training of deep neural networks for image classification, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper discusses the behavior of Stochastic Gradient Descent (SGD) during training and its ability to generalize well despite overparameterization. This makes it likely that the paper belongs to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
